1. Put Your Logo in the Static Folder
your_project/
├── static/
│   └── images/
│       └── logo.png


2. Configure settings.py for Static Files
# settings.py

STATIC_URL = '/static/'

# (Optional if not already added)
import os
STATICFILES_DIRS = [
    os.path.join(BASE_DIR, "static"),
]


3. Update the Homepage Template (e.g., home.html)
{% load static %}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Restaurant Homepage</title>
    <style>
        .logo {
            display: block;
            margin: 0 auto;
            width: 200px; /* Adjust as needed */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- Logo Display -->
    <img src="{% static 'images/logo.png' %}" alt="Restaurant Logo" class="logo">

    <!-- Rest of your homepage content -->

</body>
</html>


4. Ensure Static Files Are Collected in Production
python manage.py collectstatic
